description: Keep changes within Excalidraw's monorepo and import boundaries
alwaysApply: true
---

# Monorepo Boundaries

- Put reusable editor behavior in `packages/excalidraw/` or the appropriate lower-level package.
- Put excalidraw.com-only behavior, including collaboration, Firebase, and PWA code, in `excalidraw-app/`.
- Keep examples in `examples/` focused on integration usage.
- Lower-level packages must not depend on `@excalidraw/excalidraw` except for type-only imports.
- Within `packages/excalidraw/`, import the concrete module directly instead of importing from the package barrel.
- Never import `jotai` directly. Use `packages/excalidraw/editor-jotai.ts` in the editor or `excalidraw-app/app-jotai.ts` in the app.
- Use the existing `@excalidraw/*` path aliases from `tsconfig.json` and `vitest.config.mts`; update both files when introducing an alias.
